	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_SMOKEHOUSE">
			<Text>[ICON_FOOD] Smokehouse</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_SMOKEHOUSE_HELP">
			<Text>Each source of  [ICON_RES_BANANA] Bananas, [ICON_RES_BISON] Bison, [ICON_RES_COW] Cows, [ICON_RES_CRAB] Crab, [ICON_RES_DEER] Deer, [ICON_RES_FISH] Fish, [ICON_RES_FUR] Furs, [ICON_RES_HORSE] Horses, [ICON_RES_SHEEP] Sheep, [ICON_RES_TRUFFLES] Truffles, [ICON_RES_WHALE] Whales, and [ICON_RES_WHEAT] Wheat worked by this City produces +2 [ICON_FOOD] Food.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Allows [ICON_FOOD] Food to be moved from this city along trade routes inside your civilization.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_SMOKEHOUSE_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Smokehouse is the Danish unique building that greatly increases the food intake of a city. Unlike the Granary it replaces, the Smokehouse provides more [ICON_FOOD] Food and affects many more resources.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_SMOKEHOUSE_TEXT">
			<Text>A smokehouse is a building where usually meat or fish are cured with smoke. This helps to greatly extend the shelf life of foods, reducing waste from spoilage. The finished product might be stored in the building, sometimes for a year or more. Foods have been smoked by humans throughout history. Meats and fish are the most common smoked foods, though cheeses, vegetables, fruits, and even ingredients used to make beverages such as beer (smoked beer) can also be smoked.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>

